This paper discusses the development of a diagnostic framework for datasets to improve the quality of AI models. The paper focuses on the use of statistical and probabilistic modeling backends to generate diverse qualitative and quantitative modules for the Dataset Nutrition Label. This work is relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it aims to improve the quality of AI models. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of the Label, including the risk of using "ground truth" data, which is relevant to the field of cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the benefits of the Label for data specialists, which is relevant to the field of cryptography (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB).
